To address the issue of Django throwing an error when different apps with different models have the same table name, we need to modify the models to use database routing. This will ensure that each app points to its own database, therefore preventing the error that arises from having models with the same `db_table` in different apps.

We will do this by implementing a custom database router and modifying the settings to recognize this router.

Here is the implementation:

